ic, social, cultural, and emotional factors that divide Scots and Catalans from the larger nations to which their fortunes were joined. He offers new insights into the highly topical subject of the character and development of European nationalism, the nature of separatism, and the sense of grievance underlying the secessionist aspirations that led to the Scottish referendum of 2014, the illegal Catalan referendum of October 2017, and the resulting proclamation of an independent Catalan republic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300240719423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/doc/cover/9780300240719.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles